{"id":"beadsx-4iq","title":"No runtime validation of recentWindowHours config","description":"MEDIUM: In beadsService.ts:153-155, config value is used without validation. Negative/zero values would break filtering silently. Users can manually edit settings.json with invalid values.\n\nFix: Add runtime validation with clamping:\n```typescript\nlet recentWindowHours = config.get\u003cnumber\u003e('recentWindowHours', 1);\nif (typeof recentWindowHours !== 'number' || Number.isNaN(recentWindowHours)) {\n  log(`Warning: Invalid recentWindowHours, using default 1 hour`);\n  recentWindowHours = 1;\n} else if (recentWindowHours \u003c 0.1) {\n  recentWindowHours = 0.1;\n} else if (recentWindowHours \u003e 168) {\n  recentWindowHours = 168;\n}\n```","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-06T14:14:50.230262-06:00","updated_at":"2025-12-06T14:14:50.230262-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beadsx-4iq","depends_on_id":"beadsx-5jr","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-06T14:14:50.230865-06:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
