{"id":"beadsx-m3b","title":"Invalid date strings silently excluded from Recent filter","description":"HIGH: In beadsService.ts:160, `new Date(issue.closed_at).getTime()` returns NaN for malformed dates. When comparing `NaN \u003e= cutoffTime`, result is always false, silently excluding issues.\n\nFix: Validate parsed date and log warning when parsing fails:\n```typescript\nconst closedDate = new Date(issue.closed_at);\nconst closedTime = closedDate.getTime();\nif (Number.isNaN(closedTime)) {\n  log(`Warning: Issue ${issue.id} has invalid closed_at: \"${issue.closed_at}\"`);\n  return false;\n}\nreturn closedTime \u003e= cutoffTime;\n```","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-06T14:14:49.886329-06:00","updated_at":"2025-12-06T14:14:49.886329-06:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beadsx-m3b","depends_on_id":"beadsx-5jr","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-06T14:14:49.88742-06:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
